    "top_event": "Slip/Fall from Ladder",
    "incident_type": "Lost Time Accident (LTA >3 days)",
    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Injured party was flown via field helicopter to Cameron, LA",
      "Medical evaluation at Cameron Memorial Hospital",
      "X-rays performed to assess rib injury"
    ],
    "summary": "On October 1, 2015 at approximately 1240 hours, a contract employee sustained a minor injury at Black Elk Energy's High Island A442 A facility. The injured party had finished applying silicone caulk around a newly installed window air conditioning unit and was descending a 4' step ladder when he lost his footing (slipped). When the injured party fell, he landed on a lifting pad eye on the potable water skid which was adjacent to the 4' step ladder, striking the left side of his ribs. X-rays determined the ribs were bruised but not broken. The injured party did not return to work for the remainder of his 14 day work schedule, resulting in a lost time accident (LTA) of 8 days.",
